202 c. Any felony assault or sexual offense under Title
203 13A, Code of Alabama 1975, in which the victim is an
204 individual under 18 years of age or older, or any other
205 offense involving child abuse; or
206 d. Any comparable offense provided in this subsection
207 which was committed in any other state.
208 Section 5. (a)(1) No later than January 1, 2027, each
209 local government shall adopt a Youth Athlete Protection Policy
210 including, but not limited to: (i) standards for prohibited
211 conduct in youth sports; (ii) a code of conduct for parents,
212 spectators, coaches, and youth athletes; and (iii) a mandatory
213 reporting policy. The policy, at a minimum, shall reflect the
214 model policy developed by the department in Section 3. Each
215 local government shall provide a copy of the Youth Athlete
216 Protection Policy to all coaches employed by or volunteering
217 for the local government and parents of youth athletes
218 participating in a sport offered by that local government.
219 (2) Each local government shall require each of its
220 coaches to: (i) comply with the local government's prohibited
221 conduct policy; and (ii) annually complete mandatory reporter
222 training, as provided in Section 3.
223 (b)(1)a. Each local government shall require each coach
224 to obtain, prior to his or her employment or acceptance as a
